{"word":"ὑπερφρονέω","slug":"ὑπερφρονέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑπερφρονέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to be over-proud, to have high thoughts</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>ὑπ. τινί</el> <i>to be proud in</i> or <i>of</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to look down upon, despise</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be despised</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to think slightly of</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}